pe depending on their position within a word. Letters can exhibit up to four distinct forms corresponding to an initial, medial (middle), final, or isolated position (IMFI). While some letters show considerable variations, others remain almost identical across all four positions. Generally, letters in the same word are linked together on both sides by short horizontal lines, but six letters () can only be linked to their preceding letter. For example,  (Ararat) has only isolated forms because each letter cannot be connected to its following one. In addition, some letter combinations are written as ligatures (special shapes), notably ''''.Table of basic lettersArabic script{|class="wikitable sortable"|+ Arabic letters usage in Literary Arabic|-!colspan="2"|Common!colspan="2"|Maghrebian!rowspan="2"|Letter;brName!rowspan="2"|Letter;brName in Arabic script!rowspan="2"|Romanization of Arabic|Trans-;brliteration!rowspan="2"|Value (IPA)!colspan="3"|Contextual forms!rowspan="2"|Isolated;brform|-!Abjadī !! Hijā'ī!Abjadī !! Hijā'ī!Final!Medial!Initial|- style="text-align:center;"! !! !! !! !! !! !! !! !! !! !!;;|- style="text-align:center;"|1.|1.|1.|1.|alif|ألف| '' / '';/big; (also '';/big; '')|various,;brincluding|colspan=2||colspan=2||- style="text-align:center;"|2.|2.|2.|2.||باء|''b''|b(sometimes p in loanwords)|||||- style="text-align:center;"|22.|3.|22.|3.||تاء|''t''|t|||||- style="text-align:center;"|23.|4.|23.|4.||ثاء|''th'' (also '''')||||||- style="text-align:center;"|3.|5.|3.|5.||جيم|''j'' (also '', g;#x202f;'')| ~  ~|||||- style="text-align:center;"|8.|6.|8.|6.||حاء|''''||||||- style="text-align:center;"|24.|7.|24.|7.||خاء|''kh'' (also '', '')|x|||||- style="text-align:center;"|4.|8.|4.|8.||دال|''d''|d|colspan=2||colspan=2||- style="text-align:center;"|25.|9.|25.|9.||ذال|''dh'' (also '''')||colspan=2||colspan=2||- style="text-align:center;"|20.|10.|20.|10.||راء|''r''|r|colspan=2||colspan=2||- style="text-align:center;"|7.|11.|7.|11.|zayn /  /|زاي|''z''|z|colspan=2|